# Cross-Platform (Android / Desktop / iOS)

This game ships on **desktop, Android, and iOS**. Every feature you implement or change must work on all three unless the user explicitly scopes it to one platform.

## Default

- Put shared behavior in `core` so all launchers get it.
- Do not assume a desktop JVM, mouse/keyboard-only input, large screen, or process cwd.
- Prefer existing portable APIs (`FileUtils`, libGDX, `Game.platform`, existing UI patterns) over new platform forks.

## Before finishing any feature or change

Ask: “Does this still work on Android, desktop, and iOS?”

- [ ] Logic lives in `core` (or each platform module is updated intentionally)
- [ ] No desktop-only assumptions (cwd files, `System.exit` paths, mouse-only UX, unbounded RAM)
- [ ] Touch + keyboard/mouse still usable where UI changed
- [ ] Portrait and landscape considered if layout/UI changed
- [ ] Network / threading / lifecycle safe on mobile (pause, background, slow I/O)
- [ ] Persistence uses `FileUtils` Local — not raw `java.io.File` relative paths

## File persistence (common footgun)

Launchers set `FileUtils.setDefaultFileProperties(Files.FileType.Local, "")`. Game data must use that sandbox on every platform.

```java
// ❌ BAD — process cwd; breaks on Android/iOS
new FileOutputStream("echoes-solo/depth-5.dat");

// ✅ GOOD
FileUtils.bundleToFile("echoes-solo/depth-5.dat", bundle);
```

## Exceptions

- Launcher modules (`android/`, `ios/`, `desktop/`) may use native APIs.
- Platform-specific work only when the user asks for it; note which platforms are out of scope.
